## Overview

TCP/UDP socket communication interface for direct network communication with
instruments and devices. Supports both TCP (stream) and UDP (datagram) protocols.

## Usage

```python
from {{ interface_name }}_interface import {{ interface_name | pascal_case }}Interface

# TCP connection (default)
interface = {{ interface_name | pascal_case }}Interface(host="192.168.1.100", port=5000)
interface.connect()
interface.send(b"HELLO\n")
response = interface.receive()
interface.disconnect()

# UDP connection
interface = {{ interface_name | pascal_case }}Interface(host="192.168.1.100", port=5000, protocol="udp")
interface.connect()
interface.send(b"PING")
response = interface.receive()
interface.disconnect()
```

