## Common Pitfalls

- Ensure firewall rules allow traffic on the target port
- TCP connections may hang if the remote host is unreachable; set an appropriate timeout
- UDP does not guarantee delivery; consider adding application-level acknowledgement
- Buffer sizes should match the expected message size to avoid truncation
- Remember to handle partial receives for TCP streams (data may arrive in chunks)
